Friday is the 2 year anniversary of Mr Puckett the dog passing away. In his honor, I started Puckett Week to help survivors of domestic violence facing homelessness. 

The Mary Parrish Center offers housing to survivors along with every piece of support they need to leave an abuser, stay safe and start their life fresh again.

This week we can help.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/pAx75Dl.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>If you'd like to help domestic violence survivors facing homelessness there are two ways in Mr Puckett's memory

Donations, no matter how small

https://www.maryparrish.org/donate

I also had them set up an Amazon Wishlist if you'd like to send items directly to survivors

https://www.amazon.com/hz/wishlist/ls/3USHUHIVSINQE?ref_=wl_share

...

